arts.ttl: Finland 1-3 England: Player ratings as Three Lions cruise to victory in Helsinki
arts.sum: Arsenal's Declan Rice solidified England's victory in the latter stages of the game, tapping in a ball from Ollie Watkins to fire a low ball into the back of the net - making it 3-0. GK: Dean Henderson - 6/10 - The shot-stopper was handed his first England star against Finland and worked hard to impress.

arts.ttl: Roy Keane tears into Trent Alexander-Arnold and explains why he will be 'punished' against 'better teams' - despite England star's stunning free-kick goal against Finland
arts.sum: The Liverpool star doubled England's lead with a gorgeous strike from 25 yards in the second half, helping Lee Carsley get back to winning ways.

arts.ttl: England break national team winning record with Nations League victory over Finland
arts.sum: England set a new national team winning record with their 3-1 success over Finland in League B Group 2 of the UEFA Nations League.

arts.ttl: Jack Grealish reveals he lost £500 bet with England team-mate DURING Finland match
arts.sum: England defender Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a stunning free-kick in Sunday's 3-1 win over Finland - after Jack Grealish bet him £500 that he wouldn't find the back of the net

arts.ttl: 'You can see': Ian Wright makes claim about Angel Gomes as he shows Man United what they're missing v Finland
arts.sum: England got a big win against Finland and Ian Wright has had his say on the performance of former Manchester United midfielder Angel Gomes. Gomes...

arts.ttl: Lee Carsley gets what he asked for as three England stars prove their worth in Finland win
arts.sum: FINLAND 1-3 ENGLAND: It remains to be seen if Lee Carsley will lead England beyond next month but whatever happens next, his interim reign has yielded plenty of positives

arts.ttl: Jack Grealish reveals he made £500 offer to Trent Alexander-Arnold before Liverpool star scored stunning free-kick in England's Nations League win over Finland
arts.sum: Alexander-Arnold stepped up to take the free-kick from 25 yards and found the top corner in emphatic style to double England's lead and win £500 from Grealish.

arts.ttl: How Trent Alexander-Arnold Performed at Left-Back in Finland 1-3 England
arts.sum: England beat Finland 3-1 to return to winning ways and Trent Alexander-Arnold was on the scoresheet. He showed promise in a left-back role.

arts.ttl: Coherent England bounce back against Finland but defensive concerns remain under Lee Carsley
arts.sum: Jack Grealish shone on his return to starting lineup but still questions for Carsley after plenty of Finland chances

arts.ttl: England player ratings vs Finland: Gomes good, Trent shines
arts.sum: England returned to winning ways with a comfortable 3-1 Nations League win over Finland in Helsinki. The Three Lions issued a response to Thursday’s shock setback at home to Greece, as goals from Jack Grealish, Trent Alexander-Arnold and Declan Rice secured three points at The Olympic Stadium.
